Speech: This is—this is the final time, probably to both of your delight, that you're going to be on a stage together in this campaign.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: WALLACE
Speech: I would like to end it on a positive note.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: WALLACE
Speech: You had not agreed to closing statements, but it seems to me in a funny way that might make it more interesting because you haven't prepared closing statements.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: WALLACE
Speech: So I'd like you each to take—and we're going to put a clock up, a minute, as the final question in the final debate, to tell the American people why they should elect you to be the next president.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: WALLACE
Speech: This is another new mini-segment.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: WALLACE
Speech: Secretary Clinton, it's your turn to go first.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: CLINTON
Speech: Well, I would like to say to everyone watching tonight that I'm reaching out to all Americans—Democrats, Republicans, and independents—because we need everybody to help make our country what it should be, to grow the economy, to make it fairer, to make it work for everyone.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: CLINTON
Speech: We need your talents, your skills, your commitments, your energy, your ambition.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: CLINTON
Speech: You know, I've been privileged to see the presidency up close.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: CLINTON
Speech: And I know the awesome responsibility of protecting our country and the incredible opportunity of working to try to make life better for all of you.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: CLINTON
Speech: I have made the cause of children and families really my life's work.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: CLINTON
Speech: That's what my mission will be in the presidency.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: CLINTON
Speech: I will stand up for families against powerful interests, against corporations.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: CLINTON
Speech: I will do everything that I can to make sure that you have good jobs, with rising incomes, that your kids have good educations from preschool through college.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: CLINTON
Speech: I hope you will give me a chance to serve as your president.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: WALLACE
Speech: Secretary Clinton, thank you.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: WALLACE
Speech: Mr. Trump?

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: She's raising the money from the people she wants to control.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: Doesn't work that way.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: But when I started this campaign, I started it very strongly.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: It's called "Make America Great Again."

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: We're going to make America great.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: We have a depleted military.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: It has to be helped, has to be fixed.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: We have the greatest people on Earth in our military.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: We don't take care of our veterans.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: We take care of illegal immigrants, people that come into the country illegally, better than we take care of our vets.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: That can't happen.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: Our policemen and women are disrespected.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: We need law and order, but we need justice, too.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: Our inner cities are a disaster.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: You get shot walking to the store.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: They have no education.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: They have no jobs.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: I will do more for African-Americans and Latinos than she can ever do in 10 lifetimes.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: All she's done is talk to the African-Americans and to the Latinos, but they get the vote, and then they come back, they say, we'll see you in four years.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: We are going to make America strong again, and we are going to make America great again, and it has to start now.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: TRUMP
Speech: We cannot take four more years of Barack Obama, and that's what you get when you get her.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: WALLACE
Speech: Thank you both.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: WALLACE
Speech: [applause]  Secretary Clinton—hold on just a moment, folks.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: WALLACE
Speech: Secretary Clinton, Mr. Trump, I want to thank you both for participating in all three of these debates.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: WALLACE
Speech: That brings to an end this year's debates sponsored by the Commission on Presidential Debates.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: WALLACE
Speech: We want to thank the University of Nevada, Las Vegas, and its students for having us.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: WALLACE
Speech: Now the decision is up to you.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: WALLACE
Speech: While millions have already voted, Election Day, November 8th, is just 20 days away.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: WALLACE
Speech: One thing everyone here can agree on: We hope you will go vote.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: WALLACE
Speech: It is one of the honors and obligations of living in this great country.

Location: University of Nevada in Las Vegas
Speaker: WALLACE
Speech: Thank you, and good night.
